WEBVTT

00:00:11.116 --> 00:00:15.120
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:00:20.416 --> 00:00:22.418
Here.

00:00:27.423 --> 00:00:29.884
Hurry! That woman is… How awful.

00:00:34.222 --> 00:00:35.723
Mr. Heo, let's go.

00:00:37.267 --> 00:00:40.186
You know it'd be bad
if Mr. Kim saw me here.

00:01:10.091 --> 00:01:11.134
I'm sorry.

00:01:13.094 --> 00:01:14.137
I never imagined…

00:01:16.097 --> 00:01:17.223
I just wanted

00:01:17.891 --> 00:01:21.019
to prove to you what I saw.

00:01:28.276 --> 00:01:29.611
Please drop me off here.

00:01:30.445 --> 00:01:32.030
I'll walk the rest.

00:01:44.584 --> 00:01:46.377
Thank you for the ride.

00:01:47.420 --> 00:01:48.755
See you in tomorrow's class.

00:01:57.055 --> 00:02:00.183
Tell me the truth,
and don't you dare think about lying.

00:02:02.393 --> 00:02:05.647
Did you really not know,
or did you just pretend not to?

00:02:06.731 --> 00:02:07.565
Sorry?

00:02:08.358 --> 00:02:09.234
What do you mean?

00:02:09.734 --> 00:02:12.403
Why didn't you tell me
who Se-yun's dad is?

00:02:13.905 --> 00:02:15.698
Don't tell me you didn't know.

00:02:18.326 --> 00:02:19.452
What do you…

00:02:20.203 --> 00:02:21.496
Who is Mr. Kim?

00:02:24.082 --> 00:02:25.667
Don't know Kim Su-hun, the author?

00:03:00.868 --> 00:03:02.412
<i>Kim Su-hun, the author?</i>

00:03:03.997 --> 00:03:05.498
Kim Su-hun, the author…

00:03:07.292 --> 00:03:09.460
So Se-yun's dad is an author.

00:03:09.544 --> 00:03:10.712
No wonder.

00:03:12.463 --> 00:03:14.799
I'm not too familiar with many authors.

00:03:17.302 --> 00:03:18.386
So what?

00:03:19.470 --> 00:03:21.097
So what if he's Kim Su-hun?

00:03:22.640 --> 00:03:24.225
Is that important right now?

00:04:01.137 --> 00:04:04.057
So it was you all along, Kim Su-hun.

00:04:24.369 --> 00:04:25.578
Mom.

00:04:39.884 --> 00:04:42.345
Right, it's you.

00:05:05.952 --> 00:05:07.036
Mun-oh?

00:05:08.496 --> 00:05:10.665
You skipped class too?

00:05:22.552 --> 00:05:23.386
Oh, here.

00:05:25.012 --> 00:05:26.055
What's this?

00:05:28.266 --> 00:05:31.352
I adore this poet. How did you know?

00:05:32.186 --> 00:05:33.729
Oh my gosh.

00:05:36.649 --> 00:05:39.068
Thank you so much for this, Mun-oh.

00:05:39.152 --> 00:05:41.195
I'll see you later.

00:05:44.323 --> 00:05:46.159
-Eun-joo.
-Su-hun!

00:05:46.909 --> 00:05:47.869
Well, well.

00:05:48.911 --> 00:05:51.080
What a surprise. Where are you headed?

00:06:03.801 --> 00:06:05.720
Please don't think too much.

00:06:06.762 --> 00:06:09.765
The most important thing to me
is that you feel at peace.

00:06:10.475 --> 00:06:13.186
In our family,
nothing matters more than that.

00:07:13.996 --> 00:07:15.957
Kim Su-hun, you son of a bitch.

00:07:18.292 --> 00:07:20.294
How could you betray dear Eun-joo…

00:07:37.144 --> 00:07:43.484
We don't call everything that happens
in our daily lives an incident, do we?

00:07:43.568 --> 00:07:45.069
Regardless of size,

00:07:45.695 --> 00:07:48.656
if an event has a significant impact

00:07:49.657 --> 00:07:52.493
on the lives and actions
of the characters,

00:07:53.286 --> 00:07:57.373
then we can call it a narrative incident.

00:08:00.376 --> 00:08:02.545
And such events…

00:08:09.885 --> 00:08:11.012
always stem from…

00:08:13.681 --> 00:08:15.433
the intricate conflicts

00:08:16.475 --> 00:08:17.602
within the human mind…

00:08:26.193 --> 00:08:27.111
I'm sorry.

00:08:27.862 --> 00:08:29.363
So these conflicts…

00:08:30.323 --> 00:08:32.450
Hold on. Where was I?

00:08:42.752 --> 00:08:44.170
My office, now.

00:08:54.138 --> 00:08:55.514
You punk.

00:08:57.433 --> 00:08:59.560
Why do you always sit

00:09:00.186 --> 00:09:02.938
in the last row of the lecture hall?

00:09:04.315 --> 00:09:05.650
It's so you can daydream

00:09:07.026 --> 00:09:09.070
instead of paying attention, isn't it?

00:09:11.405 --> 00:09:13.407
You can see everything from there.

00:09:14.950 --> 00:09:18.704
A seat where I can observe everything
without being seen myself.

00:09:25.252 --> 00:09:26.087
Listen.

00:09:29.298 --> 00:09:30.883
About what happened last night.

00:09:31.884 --> 00:09:33.219
Tell me more about it.

00:09:34.095 --> 00:09:36.514
What was her name again? Min-hui?

00:09:36.597 --> 00:09:40.351
Seon Min-hui, was it?
The woman who got into that accident.

00:09:41.435 --> 00:09:42.520
And

00:09:43.479 --> 00:09:44.313
Kim Su…

00:09:45.439 --> 00:09:46.691
Se-yun's dad.

00:09:48.234 --> 00:09:49.860
What's he been doing since then?

00:09:51.112 --> 00:09:51.946
Tell me.

00:09:55.241 --> 00:09:56.075
What?

00:09:58.661 --> 00:09:59.578
You don't want to?

00:10:03.040 --> 00:10:05.710
You should at least tell <i>me</i>.

00:10:06.293 --> 00:10:09.463
I was also there last night,
thanks to you.

00:10:09.547 --> 00:10:10.506
She's dead.

00:10:16.303 --> 00:10:17.346
Dead?

00:10:18.389 --> 00:10:19.432
The police called

00:10:20.057 --> 00:10:21.475
this morning.

00:10:31.944 --> 00:10:33.028
So, in the end…

00:10:37.366 --> 00:10:38.284
In the end…

00:10:40.161 --> 00:10:41.245
So, in the end…

00:10:45.374 --> 00:10:47.877
Mr. Heo, do you know
Kim Su-hun personally?

00:10:48.377 --> 00:10:49.670
How well do you know him?

00:10:53.299 --> 00:10:54.133
What?

00:10:55.468 --> 00:10:56.844
I don't know him that well.

00:10:57.595 --> 00:11:00.639
I just know he's a famous author,
that's all.

00:11:01.140 --> 00:11:02.516
Why are you lying?

00:11:06.228 --> 00:11:07.062
What did you say?

00:11:09.064 --> 00:11:10.816
I heard you two are friends.

00:11:11.317 --> 00:11:15.237
Se-yun told me
that you hosted the special lecture

00:11:15.821 --> 00:11:17.156
he gave at school recently.

00:11:19.200 --> 00:11:20.034
Look.

00:11:20.951 --> 00:11:24.163
Do you think only friends
can host a discussion?

00:11:25.581 --> 00:11:27.333
We just went to college together.

00:11:30.085 --> 00:11:32.296
I don't know him that well. Wait.

00:11:33.798 --> 00:11:34.799
Why do you ask?

00:11:37.051 --> 00:11:38.177
Well, Mr. Kim…

00:11:44.266 --> 00:11:45.392
What about Kim Su-hun?

00:11:48.646 --> 00:11:50.481
I just wonder what kind of person he is.

00:11:51.357 --> 00:11:53.734
I liked him at first,
but now he seems strange.

00:11:54.819 --> 00:11:57.863
He's way too calm,
considering what happened last night.

00:11:58.572 --> 00:12:01.617
That's not the only strange thing.
I wrote it down here, so…

00:12:05.329 --> 00:12:07.039
-You wrote it already?
-Oh, but…

00:12:10.417 --> 00:12:11.627
It's my last assignment.

00:12:14.088 --> 00:12:15.548
You said so yesterday.

00:12:16.423 --> 00:12:18.008
That our lessons are over now.

00:12:18.843 --> 00:12:20.344
And now, with what happened…

00:12:28.394 --> 00:12:30.104
I have my convenience store gig now.

00:12:35.901 --> 00:12:37.403
Thank you,

00:12:38.863 --> 00:12:40.614
and sorry about everything, Mr. Heo.

00:12:41.115 --> 00:12:42.241
That's not…

00:12:44.618 --> 00:12:45.911
Hey, I…

00:13:17.526 --> 00:13:20.738
<i>When the line between beauty</i>
<i>and ugliness gets blurred,</i>

00:13:21.238 --> 00:13:23.782
<i>everything becomes a question mark.</i>

00:13:26.285 --> 00:13:29.246
<i>That's what the world was like</i>
<i>this morning.</i>

00:13:29.330 --> 00:13:31.498
She didn't come to work yesterday either?

00:13:33.584 --> 00:13:34.877
And without notice?

00:13:37.504 --> 00:13:39.131
Oh my, I had no idea.

00:13:39.757 --> 00:13:42.468
I called her
at least three times yesterday,

00:13:42.551 --> 00:13:44.053
but she didn't pick up.

00:13:45.220 --> 00:13:48.223
She's just being petty
because I gave her a stern talking-to.

00:13:48.724 --> 00:13:50.267
What an awful attitude.

00:13:50.768 --> 00:13:53.187
After I went out of my way
to talk to her that day.

00:13:54.104 --> 00:13:58.108
I think generosity and compassion
are wasted on people like her.

00:13:59.151 --> 00:14:01.111
I'm not letting this slide anymore.

00:14:01.195 --> 00:14:02.738
Yeah, let her quit.

00:14:03.822 --> 00:14:07.493
Didn't I tell you before
not to stress yourself out over her?

00:14:07.993 --> 00:14:09.954
I'll tell her when she comes tomorrow.

00:14:10.454 --> 00:14:13.874
You don't think
she'll be a no-show tomorrow too, do you?

00:14:15.584 --> 00:14:16.418
What you doing?

00:14:17.628 --> 00:14:19.004
It's nothing.

00:14:23.092 --> 00:14:25.094
Hey. Are you all ready to go?

00:14:26.136 --> 00:14:29.139
Just wait a bit.
I'm almost done setting the table.

00:14:30.349 --> 00:14:34.353
No complaining about side dishes today.
Especially you, Kim Se-yun.

00:14:34.436 --> 00:14:36.522
Just say "it's good," and eat.

00:14:37.815 --> 00:14:38.941
What's going on?

00:14:39.024 --> 00:14:40.776
Don't worry about it.

00:14:42.152 --> 00:14:44.822
I'll be making the side dishes
for the time being.

00:14:46.615 --> 00:14:49.451
Or we can buy them
until we hire someone new.

00:14:50.202 --> 00:14:52.413
Wait, Min-hui's quitting?

00:14:52.913 --> 00:14:54.373
Why? When did she quit?

00:14:54.456 --> 00:14:57.167
She must be sulking.
Your mom told her off.

00:14:57.251 --> 00:14:59.211
She's gone radio silent since yesterday.

00:15:01.714 --> 00:15:04.466
Why, honey?
Are you sad to hear she's quitting?

00:15:05.676 --> 00:15:08.137
No, it's not like that.
Don't worry about it.

00:15:11.432 --> 00:15:15.060
No, Kang. You should just eat up.
You'll be late for school.

00:15:17.479 --> 00:15:18.313
Kang, sit.

00:15:22.693 --> 00:15:24.278
Yes, hello?

00:15:25.529 --> 00:15:26.363
Excuse me?

00:15:28.365 --> 00:15:29.199
The police?

00:15:33.078 --> 00:15:33.912
What?

00:15:35.330 --> 00:15:36.790
What do you mean…

00:15:44.757 --> 00:15:46.008
Oh my God.

00:15:49.136 --> 00:15:51.638
-Honey, this is terrible.
-What's going on?

00:15:53.223 --> 00:15:54.058
Honey.

00:15:54.683 --> 00:15:57.770
It's Min-hui. Yesterday, she… I mean,

00:15:58.395 --> 00:15:59.730
early this morning…

00:16:00.230 --> 00:16:01.231
Min-hui?

00:16:01.315 --> 00:16:02.441
What about her?

00:16:04.818 --> 00:16:05.778
Hello?

00:16:06.278 --> 00:16:07.654
Yes, what's this about?

00:16:08.864 --> 00:16:10.616
Yes, you can tell me.

00:16:17.623 --> 00:16:18.791
What is it, Mrs. Ahn?

00:16:19.625 --> 00:16:21.168
What about Min-hui…

00:16:24.546 --> 00:16:26.256
She died in a car accident?

00:16:26.799 --> 00:16:27.925
In the ER?

00:16:31.720 --> 00:16:33.889
What do you mean "no family"?
That's impossible.

00:16:36.350 --> 00:16:37.434
Well, honestly,

00:16:37.518 --> 00:16:40.020
we don't really know much
about her family either…

00:16:43.482 --> 00:16:45.317
Yun! What…

00:16:45.400 --> 00:16:46.443
What's wrong?

00:16:46.527 --> 00:16:48.195
-Yes, let me know.
-What's wrong?

00:16:48.278 --> 00:16:50.531
-Yes.
-What's wrong?

00:16:51.031 --> 00:16:53.742
-Not the home phone. Call my cell.
-Yun, what's wrong?

00:16:53.826 --> 00:16:55.869
-Yun.
-My cell phone number is…

00:16:55.953 --> 00:16:58.288
-Easy. Can you lift his head?
-My number's 010…

00:16:59.540 --> 00:17:02.042
-248, then 5117.
-Yun?

00:17:02.126 --> 00:17:03.210
-Yes, thanks.
-Yun?

00:17:03.794 --> 00:17:07.714
Focus on my voice.
Yun, just keep breathing, will you?

00:17:12.928 --> 00:17:15.889
Do what we learned at the hospital.
Breathe. There you go.

00:17:16.473 --> 00:17:17.808
Keep rubbing his hand.

00:17:32.197 --> 00:17:33.615
Do you think he'll be okay?

00:17:34.283 --> 00:17:36.368
Maybe we should get him to a doctor?

00:17:36.451 --> 00:17:39.955
He's just in shock.
There's no need to see a doctor for that.

00:17:40.455 --> 00:17:44.168
He took a sedative,
so he'll be fine after he sleeps it off.

00:17:45.460 --> 00:17:47.629
Let's go. We should let him sleep.

00:17:55.137 --> 00:17:57.890
His problem is that he's too weak-hearted.

00:17:59.391 --> 00:18:03.061
I thought playing sports would help,
but he hasn't changed a bit.

00:18:03.562 --> 00:18:04.855
Are you okay?

00:18:07.357 --> 00:18:08.567
No.

00:18:09.067 --> 00:18:10.986
If I'm honest, I'm heartbroken too.

00:18:12.529 --> 00:18:15.532
I can't stop thinking about
how mean I was to Min-hui.

00:18:18.577 --> 00:18:20.412
That day, I shouldn't have let her

00:18:21.038 --> 00:18:22.748
walk away like that.

00:18:27.836 --> 00:18:30.631
You're overthinking again.

00:18:31.215 --> 00:18:33.258
You didn't do anything wrong.

00:18:34.843 --> 00:18:36.011
It's okay.

00:18:37.054 --> 00:18:39.556
Our lives are in the hands of fate.
It's a shame, but…

00:18:39.640 --> 00:18:43.560
<i>When the line between kindness</i>
<i>and cruelty gets blurred,</i>

00:18:44.645 --> 00:18:46.563
<i>everything becomes a question mark.</i>

00:18:59.576 --> 00:19:03.622
<i>Like that smile that harbors</i>
<i>some unknown malice.</i>

00:19:16.218 --> 00:19:17.261
"Malice"?

00:19:20.389 --> 00:19:21.306
Malice.

00:19:27.938 --> 00:19:28.939
Malice…

00:19:32.109 --> 00:19:34.111
Malice? What does he mean by that?

00:19:46.081 --> 00:19:47.124
Have a good one.

00:20:05.809 --> 00:20:06.643
Welcome…

00:20:08.687 --> 00:20:09.646
Mr. Heo?

00:20:15.485 --> 00:20:17.404
A pack of these.

00:20:19.614 --> 00:20:21.199
How did you know I worked here?

00:20:21.950 --> 00:20:25.495
You told me that you worked at
the convenience store by the intersection.

00:20:29.082 --> 00:20:30.500
Did you come here to see me?

00:20:30.584 --> 00:20:32.836
I was on my way home
and out of cigarettes.

00:20:35.881 --> 00:20:37.257
Why are you grinning?

00:20:37.341 --> 00:20:38.175
They're obvious.

00:20:39.384 --> 00:20:40.260
Your lies.

00:20:43.388 --> 00:20:44.723
What do you want to say?

00:20:46.308 --> 00:20:47.351
That's why you're here.

00:20:50.228 --> 00:20:52.439
If you're not too busy, let's talk.

00:20:58.153 --> 00:20:59.279
You know…

00:21:01.448 --> 00:21:04.951
I only said we should stop our lessons…

00:21:07.746 --> 00:21:10.999
because I got mad.

00:21:15.003 --> 00:21:15.962
What about you?

00:21:16.963 --> 00:21:20.050
Don't you think you'd regret it
if we just end them like this?

00:21:23.553 --> 00:21:24.513
I would

00:21:25.222 --> 00:21:26.765
love to continue, of course.

00:21:27.766 --> 00:21:29.309
And I want to keep writing.

00:21:32.521 --> 00:21:34.356
I just wonder if you'd be all right.

00:21:34.439 --> 00:21:35.273
About Mr. Kim…

00:21:37.109 --> 00:21:40.320
Since you know him personally,
this must be awkward.

00:21:42.155 --> 00:21:43.156
That's true.

00:21:45.700 --> 00:21:48.537
Ethically speaking,
I am conflicted about it.

00:21:50.038 --> 00:21:51.706
Even if we're not close,

00:21:52.958 --> 00:21:55.460
he's not a complete stranger either.

00:21:56.711 --> 00:21:59.756
But, for the sake of your studies,

00:22:00.257 --> 00:22:02.801
I think it'd only be my duty as a teacher

00:22:03.510 --> 00:22:06.763
to continue the lessons
as originally planned.

00:22:08.265 --> 00:22:09.266
Besides,

00:22:10.892 --> 00:22:12.352
I think it's only right…

00:22:14.813 --> 00:22:16.523
for me to be braver

00:22:17.023 --> 00:22:18.191
at times like these.

00:22:20.944 --> 00:22:22.946
As long as you're okay with it…

00:22:26.741 --> 00:22:27.784
Thank you.

00:22:28.285 --> 00:22:29.828
Thank you.

00:22:29.911 --> 00:22:31.413
Frankly speaking,

00:22:31.496 --> 00:22:34.458
it doesn't really matter to me
who Mr. Kim is.

00:22:35.834 --> 00:22:38.545
What I'm learning from you
is far more important.

00:22:43.049 --> 00:22:45.093
Now that's what I like to hear.

00:22:45.594 --> 00:22:47.137
That's the attitude.

00:22:50.098 --> 00:22:52.559
We just need to continue our lessons

00:22:53.185 --> 00:22:55.103
with that very mindset, okay?

00:23:00.150 --> 00:23:01.276
But

00:23:02.027 --> 00:23:03.236
there's no need

00:23:03.820 --> 00:23:06.406
to tell Kim Su-hun about me.

00:23:07.782 --> 00:23:08.950
You understand, right?

00:23:09.451 --> 00:23:12.204
The minute you do,
you can say goodbye to our lessons.

00:23:12.287 --> 00:23:13.538
I know, Mr. Heo.

00:23:13.622 --> 00:23:14.998
I know that much.

00:23:15.999 --> 00:23:17.626
I don't want to tell him either.

00:23:18.126 --> 00:23:20.128
I don't even want to talk
to Mr. Kim anymore.

00:23:20.212 --> 00:23:21.505
You've read what I wrote.

00:23:36.019 --> 00:23:39.564
Speaking of your assignment,

00:23:40.065 --> 00:23:42.359
what did you mean by that last bit?

00:23:42.442 --> 00:23:43.276
"Malice"?

00:23:45.320 --> 00:23:46.154
How would I know?

00:23:47.781 --> 00:23:50.158
I just wrote what I saw and felt
in the moment.

00:23:52.160 --> 00:23:55.997
Like I told you before,
you're too quick to jump to conclusions.

00:23:56.081 --> 00:23:59.584
If you're going to use a word like that,
you have to have a reason.

00:23:59.668 --> 00:24:00.502
Reason?

00:24:01.086 --> 00:24:03.213
You said those two were dating.

00:24:03.296 --> 00:24:07.217
Yet he smiled to himself
when his lover died? It doesn't add up.

00:24:07.300 --> 00:24:09.052
Are you doubting me again?

00:24:09.553 --> 00:24:10.762
I saw it as clear as day!

00:24:10.845 --> 00:24:13.223
No, I'm not doubting you.

00:24:14.140 --> 00:24:18.436
The character and plot lack
the plausibility to call it malice.

00:24:19.104 --> 00:24:21.147
First, we need to find out

00:24:21.231 --> 00:24:24.025
what happened between them
right before the accident.

00:24:25.485 --> 00:24:26.486
So,

00:24:27.779 --> 00:24:29.114
are you asking me

00:24:30.073 --> 00:24:31.157
to go to that hotel?

00:24:33.076 --> 00:24:34.202
Now you're getting it.

00:24:36.204 --> 00:24:37.539
Put differently…

00:24:40.041 --> 00:24:40.917
this is

00:24:41.918 --> 00:24:43.336
an investigative assignment.

00:24:44.838 --> 00:24:47.257
By investigating,
we'll bring realism to your story.

00:24:51.511 --> 00:24:53.471
Do you know my heart just skipped a beat?

00:24:53.972 --> 00:24:54.931
So you're telling me

00:24:55.432 --> 00:24:59.185
to go there in person
and dig into the scene, right?

00:25:00.353 --> 00:25:02.897
-Don't get so worked up. Sit.
-Yes, sir.

00:25:03.398 --> 00:25:04.899
Why are you getting so worked up?

00:25:04.983 --> 00:25:07.485
Best to stay calm,
especially in situations like this.

00:25:08.278 --> 00:25:10.947
Okay. I have some time tomorrow afternoon.

00:25:11.031 --> 00:25:12.115
All right, then.

00:25:12.824 --> 00:25:13.783
I'll be going.

00:25:15.827 --> 00:25:17.454
Would you like to come with me?

00:25:18.663 --> 00:25:19.497
Me?

00:25:21.124 --> 00:25:22.542
Why would I go there?

00:25:22.626 --> 00:25:23.668
Why not?

00:25:24.544 --> 00:25:25.920
Are you scared of losing face?

00:25:27.672 --> 00:25:30.550
Face? Please.
I have important plans tomorrow.

00:25:32.927 --> 00:25:35.263
You punk, do you think I'm lying?

00:25:38.892 --> 00:25:40.393
What are you doing tomorrow?

00:25:47.233 --> 00:25:48.568
If you aren't busy…

00:25:50.695 --> 00:25:54.449
I was thinking we could go out.
Watch a movie or something.

00:26:01.039 --> 00:26:02.957
Can't you tell?

00:26:03.792 --> 00:26:04.834
I'm…

00:26:06.920 --> 00:26:08.713
asking you out on a date.

00:26:48.253 --> 00:26:49.838
<i>Damn it, my car keys.</i>

00:26:50.422 --> 00:26:51.297
<i>My car keys.</i>

00:26:51.965 --> 00:26:53.717
<i>They're not here? Where are they?</i>

00:26:53.800 --> 00:26:56.761
<i>My darn car keys!</i>

00:27:09.107 --> 00:27:11.901
<i>Mr. Heo, I just got back from the hotel.</i>

00:27:11.985 --> 00:27:15.864
<i>If I start on my assignment now,</i>
<i>it should be in your inbox in two hours.</i>

00:27:15.947 --> 00:27:17.991
<i>There are so many shocking developments.</i>

00:27:22.954 --> 00:27:24.539
He asked you out on a date?

00:27:25.957 --> 00:27:27.625
Yesterday, out of the blue.

00:27:28.418 --> 00:27:31.463
He asked to go to the movies alone,
but that would be no fun.

00:27:32.130 --> 00:27:33.715
So I asked you to join us.

00:27:35.925 --> 00:27:38.386
Or maybe you invited us
to brag about your date.

00:27:38.470 --> 00:27:39.846
Brag? Oh, please.

00:27:42.474 --> 00:27:43.892
You're so cheeky.

00:27:44.392 --> 00:27:46.478
Can't you just turn a blind eye for once?

00:27:46.561 --> 00:27:49.689
You're not the only couple
that goes on dates.

00:27:49.773 --> 00:27:51.024
Right, honey?

00:27:56.488 --> 00:27:58.281
What are you doing? Answer me.

00:27:59.449 --> 00:28:00.450
Answer what?

00:28:04.954 --> 00:28:06.080
He's been weird lately…

00:28:06.164 --> 00:28:08.208
<i>It's been two hours.</i>
<i>Where's your assignment?</i>

00:28:09.209 --> 00:28:11.211
He's acting out of character? How?

00:28:13.087 --> 00:28:14.839
He sleeps in my room sometimes.

00:28:16.341 --> 00:28:17.175
Oh my!

00:28:17.759 --> 00:28:21.262
Wow, Mun-oh. That's great! Wow.

00:28:25.141 --> 00:28:26.726
No, this is a good thing.

00:28:26.810 --> 00:28:30.605
That explains why you've been glowing
these days, Hyeon-suk.

00:28:30.688 --> 00:28:31.523
Excuse me?

00:28:32.148 --> 00:28:34.651
What are you talking about? I always glow.

00:28:34.734 --> 00:28:37.195
-You have always been beautiful.
-Yeah.

00:28:37.695 --> 00:28:38.738
Mun-oh.

00:28:39.239 --> 00:28:43.785
Please, just be good to Hyeon-suk.
Don't leave her lonely like back then.

00:28:44.285 --> 00:28:45.912
Hey, back then?

00:28:46.412 --> 00:28:47.539
Yeah, in the past.

00:28:48.331 --> 00:28:50.708
When you had multiple miscarriages.

00:28:51.209 --> 00:28:52.919
And when you were trying IVF.

00:28:54.420 --> 00:28:56.840
Why are you bringing that up right now?

00:28:56.923 --> 00:28:58.800
Mun-oh was so inattentive then.

00:29:00.385 --> 00:29:01.928
Do you even know

00:29:02.011 --> 00:29:04.681
how lonely she was
and how much she suffered back then?

00:29:04.764 --> 00:29:07.058
Come on, honey. What's with you?

00:29:07.141 --> 00:29:08.768
What, am I wrong?

00:29:09.853 --> 00:29:11.312
That's how you were.

00:29:11.938 --> 00:29:12.939
You were exhausted…

00:29:13.022 --> 00:29:16.192
<i>I just sent you my assignment.</i>
<i>Sorry for the delay, Mr. Heo.</i>

00:29:16.276 --> 00:29:20.238
…yet you were more worried about Mun-oh's
creative slump or whatever than yourself.

00:29:20.864 --> 00:29:22.615
I'm going to go to the restroom.

00:29:22.699 --> 00:29:24.325
Yes, go ahead.

00:29:29.163 --> 00:29:30.874
I hate to tell you "I told you so,"

00:29:31.374 --> 00:29:34.252
but you were so head over heels
for a writer.

00:29:34.335 --> 00:29:35.169
Hey!

00:29:35.253 --> 00:29:39.382
He left because he's embarrassed.
How could you say that to his face?

00:29:40.008 --> 00:29:42.635
That was then. He's good to me now!

00:30:07.660 --> 00:30:08.703
<i>By then,</i>

00:30:09.287 --> 00:30:11.497
<i>the bloodstains had been</i>
<i>wiped away completely.</i>

00:30:32.894 --> 00:30:34.145
I'm not sure.

00:30:34.646 --> 00:30:36.773
I can't remember every single guest.

00:30:37.273 --> 00:30:40.777
And even if I did, I can't just give out
our guests' personal information.

00:30:40.860 --> 00:30:43.529
And the car accident
has nothing to do with our hotel.

00:30:44.197 --> 00:30:46.616
If I may, why do you ask?

00:30:47.158 --> 00:30:48.409
What's this about?

00:30:48.910 --> 00:30:50.453
I see. Thank you.

00:31:09.555 --> 00:31:11.307
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

00:31:12.684 --> 00:31:14.227
-One moment, please.
-Yes?

00:31:14.310 --> 00:31:17.438
Have you seen this man among the guests?

00:31:17.981 --> 00:31:19.148
No, I haven't.

00:31:21.442 --> 00:31:23.069
Do you recognize this man?

00:31:24.570 --> 00:31:26.155
I've never seen him before.

00:31:29.993 --> 00:31:31.202
I don't know him.

00:31:36.082 --> 00:31:37.375
I'm not sure.

00:31:44.257 --> 00:31:45.883
Whoa, sorry.

00:31:46.551 --> 00:31:47.552
Apologies.

00:31:48.219 --> 00:31:50.763
You're not allowed in here.

00:31:53.141 --> 00:31:55.393
Sir? The exit is this way.

00:31:56.477 --> 00:31:57.478
I know that.

00:32:01.524 --> 00:32:02.358
Lee Kang?

00:32:05.445 --> 00:32:07.238
Is that you? Lee Kang?

00:32:08.906 --> 00:32:09.741
Jae-sik?

00:32:12.368 --> 00:32:13.411
Jae-sik!

00:32:13.494 --> 00:32:15.163
<i>It was an incredible stroke of luck.</i>

00:32:15.246 --> 00:32:16.122
How've you been?

00:32:16.205 --> 00:32:18.249
<i>Had I not met Jae-sik at that moment,</i>

00:32:18.833 --> 00:32:21.753
<i>the truth would have stayed</i>
<i>buried in the dark forever.</i>

00:32:28.551 --> 00:32:29.677
<i>I first met Jae-sik</i>

00:32:30.678 --> 00:32:32.096
<i>last summer.</i>

00:32:37.602 --> 00:32:39.020
"Lee Kang."

00:32:39.896 --> 00:32:40.855
High school senior?

00:32:43.816 --> 00:32:46.861
Don't seniors usually spend the summer
studying at the academy?

00:32:47.737 --> 00:32:49.781
Yet you're wasting
your precious time working.

00:32:50.281 --> 00:32:51.783
What a tough life.

00:32:57.538 --> 00:32:59.290
What are you studying?

00:33:02.460 --> 00:33:03.669
The civil servant exam?

00:33:05.171 --> 00:33:06.172
"Oh Jae-sik."

00:33:06.964 --> 00:33:08.216
I'm just getting started.

00:33:10.093 --> 00:33:12.678
Actually, it's my third attempt
at starting. Fuck my life.

00:33:17.767 --> 00:33:20.269
<i>Holy crap, Yeonseo University?</i>
<i>Brainy bastard, huh?</i>

00:33:23.231 --> 00:33:25.066
What about you? The civil servant exam.

00:33:26.484 --> 00:33:27.318
Not yet.

00:33:28.194 --> 00:33:29.946
I'm not giving up. Don't write me off.

00:33:30.696 --> 00:33:33.449
Write you off? Never.
You're cool just as you are.

00:33:35.326 --> 00:33:36.160
Really?

00:33:37.370 --> 00:33:40.414
I mean, yeah.
Working at the hotel isn't so bad.

00:33:42.125 --> 00:33:45.086
What about that car accident?
What do you want to know?

00:33:45.586 --> 00:33:47.713
Well, it's a long story.

00:33:48.381 --> 00:33:51.592
It's strictly personal.
I kind of knew the woman who died.

00:33:52.510 --> 00:33:54.262
Is that right?

00:33:54.762 --> 00:33:55.805
You knew her?

00:33:56.389 --> 00:33:58.182
Yeah, I just feel bad for her.

00:33:59.016 --> 00:34:01.978
I'd like to know what happened
before the accident,

00:34:03.604 --> 00:34:05.189
but no one will tell me shit.

00:34:07.817 --> 00:34:08.818
I bet no one else…

00:34:10.528 --> 00:34:12.196
knows more about it than I do.

00:34:14.532 --> 00:34:15.366
Really?

00:34:17.660 --> 00:34:18.578
I

00:34:20.079 --> 00:34:21.664
even witnessed the accident.

00:34:23.541 --> 00:34:25.835
<i>I was on my way home from work.</i>

00:34:27.670 --> 00:34:29.463
Talk to me before you go!

00:34:30.256 --> 00:34:31.090
I'm not talking…

00:34:31.174 --> 00:34:34.844
<i>I recognized them right away.</i>

00:34:34.927 --> 00:34:35.928
<i>Especially…</i>

00:34:36.012 --> 00:34:36.846
Min-hui!

00:34:36.929 --> 00:34:37.930
<i>…that man.</i>

00:34:39.015 --> 00:34:40.725
What? You scared?

00:34:41.517 --> 00:34:44.145
Just wait and see the shit I pull.

00:34:52.612 --> 00:34:54.322
-Call an ambulance.
-Holy crap.

00:34:54.405 --> 00:34:56.490
-What the…
-Someone call an ambulance!

00:34:56.574 --> 00:34:58.034
-We need an ambulance.
-My God!

00:34:58.117 --> 00:34:59.994
-A car accident.
-She came out of nowhere!

00:35:00.077 --> 00:35:01.746
Yeah, all of a sudden.

00:35:05.499 --> 00:35:06.584
That man.

00:35:07.251 --> 00:35:08.085
Who was he?

00:35:09.212 --> 00:35:10.254
That man

00:35:10.880 --> 00:35:13.424
<i>was a regular at our suite.</i>

00:35:15.259 --> 00:35:17.762
"A regular at the hotel suite"?

00:35:20.640 --> 00:35:21.766
Kim Su-hun was?

00:35:24.435 --> 00:35:26.395
<i>He came three or four times a month</i>

00:35:27.146 --> 00:35:29.106
<i>and always reserved </i>that <i>room.</i>

00:35:29.190 --> 00:35:31.108
<i>But the funny thing is,</i>

00:35:31.692 --> 00:35:33.694
<i>he would always order top-shelf wine</i>

00:35:33.778 --> 00:35:36.155
<i>with a side of cheap ice cream</i>
<i>through room service.</i>

00:35:36.239 --> 00:35:39.492
<i>Wait, cheap ice cream? Why?</i>

00:35:39.575 --> 00:35:42.870
<i>I wouldn't know.</i>
<i>I guess that's up to our imaginations.</i>

00:35:46.082 --> 00:35:48.376
Hello, sir. Room service.

00:35:50.586 --> 00:35:51.837
Thank you, sir.

00:35:55.591 --> 00:35:57.677
<i>The woman's outfit changed every time.</i>

00:35:58.177 --> 00:36:01.722
<i>A nurse costume one day.</i>
<i>A bunny, the next.</i>

00:36:02.223 --> 00:36:05.101
<i>And another day, a schoolgirl uniform.</i>

00:36:05.184 --> 00:36:06.435
Yeah, Mr. Choi.

00:36:07.520 --> 00:36:08.604
Not at all.

00:36:09.563 --> 00:36:10.982
I'm on a trip.

00:36:12.316 --> 00:36:14.652
No, just me without my wife.

00:36:15.653 --> 00:36:17.154
No, I'm not writing.

00:36:17.989 --> 00:36:19.448
I don't have anything written.

00:36:20.199 --> 00:36:23.202
<i>-The truth is, he's an author.</i>
-Just needed some inspiration.

00:36:23.995 --> 00:36:26.247
<i>He probably thought</i>
<i>someone like me wouldn't know.</i>

00:36:27.456 --> 00:36:28.582
<i>He's an author?</i>

00:36:29.208 --> 00:36:30.418
Yeah.

00:36:43.306 --> 00:36:45.057
Man, how could an author…

00:36:45.766 --> 00:36:47.184
And he's married, you say?

00:36:48.394 --> 00:36:50.271
Bastards like him are the worst.

00:36:50.354 --> 00:36:53.190
They act respectable in public
but are sick pervs in private.

00:36:54.400 --> 00:36:58.487
So that's what he was doing that day too?
The day of the accident?

00:36:58.988 --> 00:36:59.905
No.

00:37:00.406 --> 00:37:01.449
That day was

00:37:02.283 --> 00:37:03.492
a little different.

00:37:04.076 --> 00:37:05.661
A bit unusual, you could say.

00:37:06.829 --> 00:37:08.039
Unusual?

00:37:08.539 --> 00:37:12.084
Yeah. The noises I heard that day
were a little different.

00:37:12.960 --> 00:37:14.920
I didn't mean to eavesdrop, but…

00:37:17.298 --> 00:37:18.632
What different noises?

00:37:20.259 --> 00:37:21.093
Well, you see…

00:37:24.138 --> 00:37:25.264
WIFE

00:37:30.686 --> 00:37:33.689
What I heard was…

00:37:34.982 --> 00:37:35.816
PARK HYEONG-JONG

00:37:35.900 --> 00:37:38.152
Why are you people doing this?

00:37:41.947 --> 00:37:43.240
Professor Park, what is it?

00:37:43.324 --> 00:37:45.117
<i>Mun-oh, where are you?</i>

00:37:45.618 --> 00:37:47.244
<i>Come on, why aren't you back yet?</i>

00:37:47.328 --> 00:37:49.997
I'll be back soon. What is it?

00:37:50.081 --> 00:37:52.917
<i>Mun-oh, guess who</i>
<i>is here with us right now?</i>

00:37:53.417 --> 00:37:55.294
<i>Do you know who we just bumped into?</i>

00:37:56.045 --> 00:37:57.838
What are you talking about?

00:38:03.761 --> 00:38:04.762
Wait, who?

00:38:09.058 --> 00:38:10.726
Let's get one altogether.

00:38:11.268 --> 00:38:13.229
Three, two, one.

00:38:13.312 --> 00:38:14.146
There you are.

00:38:14.647 --> 00:38:15.856
Hey, Mun-oh.

00:38:16.857 --> 00:38:19.026
Fancy seeing you here, huh?

00:38:19.860 --> 00:38:20.903
How have you been?

00:38:21.695 --> 00:38:22.530
Why are you here?

00:38:22.613 --> 00:38:24.115
A surprise, isn't it?

00:38:24.615 --> 00:38:28.411
I spotted him on his way home
from a meeting with a publishing house

00:38:28.494 --> 00:38:30.413
and asked him to join.

00:38:30.496 --> 00:38:31.914
A publishing house?

00:38:33.416 --> 00:38:36.919
What took you so long in the restroom?
What were you doing?

00:38:37.002 --> 00:38:38.921
You didn't even answer my call.

00:38:40.005 --> 00:38:41.298
It wasn't that long.

00:38:41.382 --> 00:38:44.427
Anyway, I hope
I'm not interrupting your fun.

00:38:44.510 --> 00:38:45.344
Not at all.

00:38:45.428 --> 00:38:48.848
You're not interrupting at all.
I'm so excited right now.

00:38:48.931 --> 00:38:51.100
Meeting you has been
the highlight of the day.

00:38:51.183 --> 00:38:52.059
Absolutely.

00:38:52.143 --> 00:38:55.062
It's always an honor
to be in your company.

00:38:55.563 --> 00:38:59.483
He's talked about you a lot
since that lecture.

00:38:59.567 --> 00:39:04.238
He's been bragging to everyone
about the pleasure of meeting you.

00:39:05.406 --> 00:39:06.740
I see.

00:39:07.450 --> 00:39:10.202
This is the first I've heard
about the lecture.

00:39:12.121 --> 00:39:15.374
That's how this one is.
Always so reserved.

00:39:15.875 --> 00:39:18.836
I didn't even know
that you two were in college together.

00:39:19.336 --> 00:39:22.548
Is that right? Eun-joo and I
talked about you from time to time.

00:39:24.425 --> 00:39:25.551
Eun-joo?

00:39:26.635 --> 00:39:29.346
My wife went to the same school.
She's Mun-oh's junior.

00:39:34.852 --> 00:39:36.645
You two talked about me?

00:39:40.983 --> 00:39:42.860
And how is Eun-joo?

00:39:42.943 --> 00:39:44.737
Yeah, she's doing well.

00:39:44.820 --> 00:39:47.490
Actually, my second kid
is attending Yeonseo University.

00:39:47.573 --> 00:39:51.494
Turns out he's in your class.
So we talked about you sometimes.

00:39:53.704 --> 00:39:54.705
I see.

00:39:55.456 --> 00:39:56.790
That's news to me.

00:39:58.792 --> 00:40:02.046
What was he like back in university?

00:40:05.508 --> 00:40:07.468
Well, he was pretty reserved.

00:40:08.135 --> 00:40:12.223
Always sitting in the last row
of the lecture hall, like an observer.

00:40:12.306 --> 00:40:14.517
It was rather cunning.

00:40:15.059 --> 00:40:16.560
But that's also Mun-oh's charm.

00:40:16.644 --> 00:40:18.521
So you haven't changed a bit.

00:40:22.816 --> 00:40:26.153
And why did you meet with
the president of that publishing house?

00:40:27.029 --> 00:40:28.322
To discuss your next book?

00:40:28.405 --> 00:40:32.284
Not my next book. He's already
talking about the one that'll come after.

00:40:32.368 --> 00:40:35.162
But I need ideas for my next book
or the one after that.

00:40:36.080 --> 00:40:36.997
Speaking of,

00:40:37.998 --> 00:40:41.126
where <i>do </i>you usually get your ideas from?

00:40:43.921 --> 00:40:46.340
Where do you find new inspiration?

00:40:47.925 --> 00:40:49.176
Well, that's…

00:40:50.803 --> 00:40:53.389
What? Is it awkward to share?

00:40:55.015 --> 00:40:56.850
I'm just curious.

00:40:59.687 --> 00:41:01.146
Perhaps you

00:41:02.565 --> 00:41:05.776
travel to new places

00:41:06.694 --> 00:41:07.611
or…

00:41:10.614 --> 00:41:11.991
meet someone new

00:41:12.074 --> 00:41:14.660
and experience a thrilling deviation
from everyday life.

00:41:18.747 --> 00:41:21.125
I wouldn't call it
a deviation from my everyday life,

00:41:22.668 --> 00:41:25.337
but I do travel a lot. Why do you ask?

00:41:28.132 --> 00:41:29.216
The truth is,

00:41:29.758 --> 00:41:33.470
he's asking
because he's genuinely curious.

00:41:34.346 --> 00:41:37.600
He's been in a slump for a long time
since writing his first novel.

00:41:38.225 --> 00:41:39.643
So he's just curious

00:41:39.727 --> 00:41:42.146
how you do it.

00:41:43.397 --> 00:41:44.231
Is that so?

00:41:46.984 --> 00:41:48.319
<i>Why the hell?</i>

00:41:48.902 --> 00:41:50.237
Why the hell?

00:41:50.321 --> 00:41:51.989
Why did you say that crap, huh?

00:41:52.072 --> 00:41:56.118
Why would you say that crap about me
being in a slump in front of that bastard?

00:41:56.201 --> 00:41:58.162
And why didn't you tell me?

00:41:58.245 --> 00:42:00.914
Why did you hide the fact
that you went to school with him?

00:42:00.998 --> 00:42:01.832
What?

00:42:01.915 --> 00:42:05.294
Did you not want to even say his name
after he stole the girl you liked?

00:42:05.377 --> 00:42:07.880
-What did you say?
-That's her name, isn't it?

00:42:08.547 --> 00:42:10.716
Ahn Eun-joo, Kim Su-hun's wife!

00:42:11.550 --> 00:42:13.886
Who is she? Who even is she to you?

00:42:13.969 --> 00:42:17.097
You said it was all in the past.
What, still got feelings for her?

00:42:17.181 --> 00:42:19.808
Why do you keep hiding things from me?
I hate that!

00:42:19.892 --> 00:42:21.810
Hiding what? It's not like that.

00:42:23.062 --> 00:42:25.689
Or do you really have
an inferiority complex toward him?

00:42:26.690 --> 00:42:28.108
Is that why you didn't tell me?

00:42:28.192 --> 00:42:29.943
Are you done?

00:42:32.529 --> 00:42:36.075
Do you know what a son of a bitch
that bastard Kim Su-hun is?

00:42:43.957 --> 00:42:46.960
How am I supposed to know
if you don't tell me?

00:43:22.287 --> 00:43:24.248
<i>It was an unusual day.</i>

00:43:24.748 --> 00:43:27.334
<i>The noises I heard that day</i>
<i>were a little different.</i>

00:43:27.418 --> 00:43:30.045
<i>How? What different noises?</i>

00:43:31.547 --> 00:43:33.048
-Let go!
-Cut it out!

00:43:33.132 --> 00:43:35.300
Should I call your family?
Want me to call?

00:43:35.384 --> 00:43:38.512
Are you threatening me?
Keep testing me like this, and you'll pay!

00:43:38.595 --> 00:43:42.182
What? I'll pay?
And how exactly will you make me pay?

00:43:42.683 --> 00:43:44.643
Fine, you son of a bitch!

00:43:44.727 --> 00:43:46.270
Do whatever you want!

00:43:46.353 --> 00:43:48.814
I'll expose you for who you really are!

00:43:48.897 --> 00:43:50.065
I even have proof!

00:43:50.149 --> 00:43:52.484
<i>-So they were fighting?</i>
<i>-</i>I have proof right here!

00:43:52.568 --> 00:43:55.362
No, not so much fighting.

00:43:55.863 --> 00:43:58.574
More like hurling threats at each other.

00:43:59.074 --> 00:44:00.075
Threats?

00:44:01.535 --> 00:44:04.747
And what was it like
when you went into the room?

00:44:05.831 --> 00:44:08.083
He told me to leave the tray
by the door that day.

00:44:10.669 --> 00:44:12.504
I wonder what threats she made.

00:44:13.464 --> 00:44:15.382
And what was the proof she mentioned?

00:44:16.925 --> 00:44:19.553
Hello? Yes, I'll head back right away.

00:44:19.636 --> 00:44:20.637
Okay.

00:44:22.848 --> 00:44:24.808
-I should get back.
-Sure, Jae-sik.

00:44:25.517 --> 00:44:29.021
-Sorry I kept you for so long.
-No, this was fun. It was nice seeing you.

00:44:29.521 --> 00:44:30.647
-See you soon.
-Yeah.

00:44:30.731 --> 00:44:32.941
Come visit me. I'll be here, okay?

00:44:33.025 --> 00:44:33.984
See you.

00:44:36.445 --> 00:44:37.613
Right, yesterday.

00:44:38.405 --> 00:44:40.908
A guy about your age
came to the hotel yesterday.

00:44:41.450 --> 00:44:42.284
What?

00:44:42.367 --> 00:44:45.662
He asked if anything had happened
before the accident. Just like you.

00:44:48.749 --> 00:44:49.708
Really?

00:44:50.542 --> 00:44:51.376
Who was he?

00:44:52.211 --> 00:44:53.045
I don't know.

00:44:53.545 --> 00:44:56.298
But he asked me
something strange at the end.

00:44:58.008 --> 00:44:59.802
If it was really a car accident,

00:45:01.136 --> 00:45:03.138
or if it could have been a murder.

00:45:04.640 --> 00:45:06.225
-A murder?
-Yeah.

00:45:06.892 --> 00:45:08.685
It threw me off at first too.

00:45:08.769 --> 00:45:10.938
I witnessed the accident myself,
after all.

00:45:11.647 --> 00:45:16.902
But I thought hard about it after he left,
and something felt off.

00:45:18.070 --> 00:45:19.071
Don't you think?

00:45:19.154 --> 00:45:21.406
He wouldn't have known
the two of them fought.

00:45:21.990 --> 00:45:23.492
I didn't tell him either.

00:45:24.243 --> 00:45:28.038
So why did he suddenly bring up
the possibility of murder?

00:45:28.914 --> 00:45:30.123
What does he know?

00:45:30.874 --> 00:45:32.125
What does he suspect?

00:45:40.843 --> 00:45:42.010
Murder?

00:46:04.741 --> 00:46:07.202
Did you think this would be enough
to get rid of me?

00:46:08.704 --> 00:46:10.414
You crazy bitch!

00:46:20.173 --> 00:46:21.550
-Let go!
-Cut it out!

00:46:21.633 --> 00:46:23.802
Should I call your family?
Want me to call?

00:46:23.886 --> 00:46:27.139
Are you threatening me?
Keep testing me like this, and you'll pay!

00:46:27.222 --> 00:46:30.726
What? I'll pay?
And how exactly will you make me pay?

00:46:31.226 --> 00:46:33.186
Fine, you son of a bitch!

00:46:33.270 --> 00:46:34.605
Do whatever you want!

00:46:34.688 --> 00:46:37.107
I'll expose you for who you really are!

00:46:37.190 --> 00:46:39.776
I even have proof! I have proof right--

00:47:38.001 --> 00:47:39.378
Kim Su-hun.

00:47:42.047 --> 00:47:43.674
What have you…

00:47:45.926 --> 00:47:47.636
What did you do?

00:47:50.013 --> 00:47:51.890
What have you done?

00:48:00.941 --> 00:48:01.858
Hurry.

00:48:07.364 --> 00:48:08.198
Hey, Lee Kang!

00:48:08.949 --> 00:48:10.742
Find that young man.

00:48:11.368 --> 00:48:13.537
<i>Mr. Heo? What time is--</i>

00:48:14.371 --> 00:48:16.999
No, we need to know who that guy is!

00:48:17.082 --> 00:48:19.793
The young man who brought up
the possibility of murder.

00:48:20.794 --> 00:48:23.505
Go back to the hotel tomorrow
and try to find out who he is.

00:48:24.006 --> 00:48:27.259
Check all the security footage
if you have to. Then we're good.

00:48:28.927 --> 00:48:31.513
Then we'll know what that proof is.

00:48:32.014 --> 00:48:34.141
<i>Mr. Heo, please calm down.</i>

00:48:34.891 --> 00:48:37.060
You <i>told me not to get</i>
<i>all worked up, remember?</i>

00:48:37.644 --> 00:48:41.231
<i>I was going to tell you tomorrow anyway…</i>

00:48:43.358 --> 00:48:45.318
<i>but I think I know who he is.</i>

00:48:46.069 --> 00:48:47.029
What did you say?

00:50:20.330 --> 00:50:21.164
Sis?

00:50:27.254 --> 00:50:28.338
Dad…

00:50:33.510 --> 00:50:35.053
killed someone.

00:50:44.479 --> 00:50:45.772
I said Dad…

00:50:50.902 --> 00:50:52.571
killed someone.

00:51:01.872 --> 00:51:04.875
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:53:30.979 --> 00:53:35.984
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi